cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the mining of tweet features and their effectiveness in terms of user engagement. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the analysis of large amounts of data to extract relevant information. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves the analysis of natural language in tweets. It could also be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it relates to the impact of social media on society. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Software Development) as it relates to the development of applications based on tweet features.
